org.apache.accumulo.core.client.mapreduce

Class AccumuloRowInputFormat

  • java.lang.Object
    • <any>
      • org.apache.accumulo.core.client.mapreduce.AbstractInputFormat<K,V>
        • org.apache.accumulo.core.client.mapreduce.InputFormatBase<Text,PeekingIterator<java.util.Map.Entry<Key,Value>>>
          • org.apache.accumulo.core.client.mapreduce.AccumuloRowInputFormat

  • public class AccumuloRowInputFormat
extends InputFormatBase<Text,PeekingIterator<java.util.Map.Entry<Key,Value>>>
    This class allows MapReduce jobs to use Accumulo as the source of data. This InputFormat provides row names as Text as keys, and a corresponding PeekingIterator as a value, which in turn makes the Key/Value pairs for that row available to the Map function. The user must specify the following via static configurator methods:
    • AbstractInputFormat.setConnectorInfo(Job, String, AuthenticationToken)
    • InputFormatBase.setInputTableName(Job, String)
    • AbstractInputFormat.setScanAuthorizations(Job, Authorizations)
    • AbstractInputFormat.setZooKeeperInstance(Job, ClientConfiguration)
    Other static methods are optional.
